pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 456863734, 'comment_body': 'Please change the name to `projectWidth` and `projectHeight`. Suggestion: in case width and height are not available, you are handing over the screen dimensions from `CBSpriteNode`. This is a great idea, however when doing so, the `screenRatio` will always be 1 -- the identity element of the multiplication and division so that is fine. I would suggest making `projectWidth` and `projectHeight` optional and set the `screenRatio` directly in those cases (this can make the code in `CBSpriteNode` more readable and prevents calling the initializer in three code execution paths). Another advantage is that we can test this case directly in `PenConfigurationTests`. What do you think?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 19, 5, 45, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 456863762, 'comment_body': 'Please add a test to `CBSpriteNodeTests` to verify that the `PenConfiguration` is receiving the proper width and height.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 19, 5, 45, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 456869582, 'comment_body': 'This is a really good idea. Thanks!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 19, 6, 53, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'neel-makhecha', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460486196, 'comment_body': 'One more thing: can we use `CGFloat` here directly instead of having to convert data types at every call?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 6, 33, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 460493389, 'comment_body': "Yeah, that's true. Thanks!\r\nI have pushed with that change. Please review it. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 26, 7, 48, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'neel-makhecha', 'type': 'User'}]

I would suggest to always use `self.position`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 3, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429521559, 'comment_body': 'Please move this file to the `Scene` subfolder. Along with this please also move the `SceneTests`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 4, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429521600, 'comment_body': 'Do we really need to have a `project` in this test?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 5, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429521647, 'comment_body': 'The update method of the scene has been tested already thoroughly. Do we really need a scene here for this test? I would suggest to call the update method of the `CBSpriteNode` directly.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 6, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429521710, 'comment_body': 'Please use `XCTFail` with a meaningful message so that it is clear why the test fails. You can then remove your comment.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 7, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429521978, 'comment_body': 'Please try to use as little "dependencies" in your test as possible. The test should not fail whenever the `SetXBrick` or the `WhenScript` have a problem. The test should be independent of these autonomous Bricks. Luckily, this functionality can be tested independently which would make the test more readable and also less error-prone. My suggestion would be update the SpriteNode's position directly (`spriteNode.position = `).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 23, 7, 12, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429600963, 'comment_body': 'Please also assert the number of children before executing your test setup is the same then after.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 35, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429600993, 'comment_body': 'Again, here please assert that before calling the update methods, the number of children were equal to 1.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 36, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429601079, 'comment_body': 'Can you also assert that the line was correctly drawn starting from the `previousPoint`?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 38, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429601109, 'comment_body': 'Please also verify the position of the second line and whether it can also be retrieved by the same name.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 39, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429601138, 'comment_body': 'I think calling this method once should be enough. Can you maybe set the `previousPosition` directly?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 40, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429601150, 'comment_body': 'I think calling this method once should be enough.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 40, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429601155, 'comment_body': 'Good test! Just again please check that before executing the update method the number of children were equal to document that nothing has changed.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 24, 5, 40, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429997288, 'comment_body': 'Please use `Double.epsilon` instead of `0.0001`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 25, 15, 46, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 429997438, 'comment_body': 'Please create a private method to avoid code duplications (e.g., below the `setUp`).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 25, 15, 46, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 430000808, 'comment_body': 'Very good idea to make a separate class for this node. Please add a test `LineShapeNodeTests` to verify the behavior.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 25, 15, 56, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 430170830, 'comment_body': 'Thanks for adding this test. For me it looks like this test is only comparing the end point of the path, which I think can be improved, also taking the start point into consideration. Consider comparing an expected path with the actual path, pseudo code:

```
let expectedPath = path from pathStartPoint to pathEndPoint
XCTAssertEqual(line.path, expectedPath)
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 26, 5, 55, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 431269533, 'comment_body': 'Please make it `let` and (or if not possible just) remove the implicit force unwrapping.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 27, 16, 15, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 431271057, 'comment_body': 'In this test it is enough to verify whether the `previousPosition` of the `penConfiguration` is set, I think there is no need to verify the actual children since this is already thoroughly tested in the other tests.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 27, 16, 17, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 423455970, 'comment_body': 'Please try to avoid duplicated code and move the `SpriteObject`, `VariablesContainer`, `Project`, `Script`, `Brick` and `ChangeVariableBrickCell` to a common setup method.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 4, 32, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423456190, 'comment_body': 'I would suggest to rename these variables to `objectVariable1`, `objectVariable2`, `projectVariable` which makes it more readable because you directly know which variable is available at which scope.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 4, 33, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423456974, 'comment_body': 'This test also passes if `allVariables` returns something different than an array of `UserVariable` and `brickCellVariableData` does not contain any values. This should not be the case. Remove the conditional `if let` cast here -- I would recommend to add the asserts directly for the `UserVariables` (e.g., `XCTAssertEqual(kLocalizedNewElement, values[0])`, `XCTAssertEqual(userVariable1.name, values[1])`). This makes it more readable.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 4, 36, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423458015, 'comment_body': 'Please remove the `sorted` here. The order plays a critical role.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 4, 41, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423614170, 'comment_body': "I have now removed `sorted` and as per `allVariables` method of `VariablesContainer`, I have assumed that program variables will be listed first, then the object variables and then other variables which aren't in the VariablesContainer. So what I understand from this is: this order needs to be maintained also when refactoring is done to these methods in future. Please correct me if I misunderstood. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 10, 1, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'neel-makhecha', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423720320, 'comment_body': 'Thanks for your changes! Please remove this method, since this case should never happen in reality and thus should also not be documented. But there is one scenario missing: please add a test with a second SpriteObject containing one (local) variable and make sure that this variable is not included in the list. General suggestion: Replace `testInitWithFrame` with `testValues`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 13, 11, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424001136, 'comment_body': 'Please review the latest commit. Here, Instead of adding a separate test I tested that scenario by making sure the count remains 4 and compared each element. If I add a separate method for the same, I will require to declare a new VariablesContainer or add a new local variable of spriteObject2 in the existing VariablesContainer instance inside the new method and testing it in a similar way as in other tests. So I thought this to be a better way. Please let me know if this will be okay. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 20, 5, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'neel-makhecha', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424336566, 'comment_body': 'Adding the comparison with _4_ is a good idea. Also the test seems to be alright. In general I would suggest to test one logical behavior in one single test. This makes debugging much easier in case of a test failure. But since these tests are not too complex, that is alright.\r\n\r\nHowever, please also add one test verifying the behavior when no variables are available. Also: I do not understand why you named the methods _WhenObjectVariableInContainer_ and _WhenProgramVariableInContainer_. As far as I can see both methods have the same variables in the container but different variables in the Brick.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 13, 10, 30, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'm-herold', 'type': 'User'}]

### Your checklist for this pull request
Please review the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/Catrobat/Catty/blob/develop/README.md) and [wiki pages](https://github.com/Catrobat/Catroid/wiki/) of this repository.

- [ ] Include the name of the Jira ticket in the PR’s title
- [ ] Verify that the Jira ticket is in the status *Ready for Development*
- [ ] Include a summary of the changes plus the relevant context
- [ ] Choose the proper base branch (*develop*)
- [ ] Confirm that the changes follow the project’s coding guidelines
- [ ] Verify that the changes generate no compiler or linter warnings
- [ ] Perform a self-review of the changes
- [ ] Verify to commit no other files than the intentionally changed ones
- [ ] Include reasonable and readable tests verifying the added or changed behavior
- [ ] Confirm that new and existing unit tests pass locally
- [ ] Check that the commits’ message style matches the [project’s guideline](https://github.com/Catrobat/Catroid/wiki/Commit-Message-Guidelines)
- [ ] Stick to the project’s git workflow (rebase and squash your commits)
- [ ] Verify that your changes do not have any conflicts with the base branch
- [ ] After the PR, verify that all CI checks have passed
- [ ] Post a message in the *#catty* [Slack channel](https://catrobat.slack.com) and ask for a code reviewer
